.TH ABRAFLEXI-MATCHER-INIT 1 "July 17, 2026" "abraflexi-matcher" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
abraflexi-matcher-init \- Create the AbraFlexi labels and document types required by the matcher scripts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B abraflexi-matcher-init
[OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abraflexi-matcher-init
checks that the AbraFlexi labels used to flag overpaid, missing-invoice
and unidentified payments exist in the company, creating any that are
missing. It also checks (and, if configured, creates) the document types
used for automatic settlement of overpayments and partial payments. Run
it once after installing the package and after connecting a new AbraFlexi
company, before scheduling any of the matcher scripts.
.SH OPTIONS
This script uses environment variables for configuration.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_URL
AbraFlexi server URL
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_LOGIN
AbraFlexi login username
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PASSWORD
AbraFlexi password
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_COMPANY
AbraFlexi company code
.TP
.B MATCHER_LABEL_PREPLATEK
Label used to mark invoices paid more than the required amount (default: PREPLATEK).
.TP
.B MATCHER_LABEL_CHYBIFAKTURA
Label used to mark payments for which no invoice was found (default: CHYBIFAKTURA).
.TP
.B MATCHER_LABEL_NEIDENTIFIKOVANO
Label used to mark payments that could not be identified at all (default: NEIDENTIFIKOVANO).
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_OVERPAY
Document type code to create/use for automatic overpayment settlement; empty (default) = skip.
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PARTIAL_CREDIT
Document type code to create/use for converting partial payments to credit; empty (default) = skip.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR abraflexi-matcher (1),
.BR abraflexi-matcher-in (1),
.BR abraflexi-matcher-out (1)
